cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its methods, please cite it as below."
title: "Balloon Squeeze: a replay-isolated, de-confounded instrument for measuring deception displacement across an audit boundary"
abstract: >-
  A deterministic, mock-first research instrument for replay-isolated causal
  estimates of deception displacement in LLM agents, pairing a within-world
  replay design with a de-confounding protocol and a pre-committed kill rule.
  Ships two standalone MIT kits: noisyjudge (class-stratified,
  judge-error-corrected contrast estimation) and deconfound (a blind-classifier
  label-leakage audit for A/B contrasts).
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Lonkins"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Lonkins/balloon-squeeze"
url: "https://github.com/Lonkins/balloon-squeeze"
license: MIT
version: "0.1.0"
keywords:
  - ai-safety
  - deception
  - scalable-oversight
  - llm-as-judge
  - construct-validity
  - measurement
